race.comment: CHASING APHRODITE (1) has been in the placings at his last two, most recently beaten a lip over 2200m at Hamilton at his third run back. Has the blinkers on for the first time and will be poised just off the lead. Ready to win. CABLE DANCER (5) went close at Moonee Valley and then didn't quite run out the staying trip at Geelong. He tumbles in weight at this level and Bates rides for the first time. Has the blinkers on again and he can bounce back into the finish. COMMANDER HARRY (3) is also third-up and ready to show his best. Finally draws an inside barrier and deserves plenty of consideration. MICKIO (6) always puts in and will run it right out.
